    {
        "content": "<p>There is a very similar question somewhere on MathOverflow.<br>\nI admit I don't quite understand the motivation--such a \"universal property\" would only determine the limit \"up to adjunction\", or something--is that the kind of thing you want?</p>",
        "id": 276461945,
        "sender_full_name": "Reid Barton",
        "timestamp": 1648121404
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I don't <em>want</em> it, but I've stumbled upon 'laxer coproducts' in the wild, and I thought they were lax colimits until I realized laxness was somewhere else<br>\nLater I will post here the example I have</p>",
        "id": 276465974,
